# Shell scripts run INSIDE Linux containers (keycloak entrypoint + init,
# postgres-init, etc.). They MUST stay LF on every OS — a Windows checkout
# with core.autocrlf=true rewrites them to CRLF, which breaks the `#!/bin/sh`
# shebang and `set -eu` and fails the keycloak-init / postgres-init containers.
*.sh text eol=lf
